SUMMARIZER="C">

The 1990 Los Angeles Marathon has an impressive list of commercial sponsors. 
Mercedes-Benz of North America is the presenting sponsor of the race, making it one of 
ten companies that not only pay to be called sponsor, but also put money outright into the 
race or provide products and services.

The marathon is not yet a world-class event, but it is the best-marketed, slickest and 
sponsor-driven of the world's major marathons. President Bill Burke and Vice President 
Marie Patrick who have marketing backgrounds drive the race's marketing philosophy.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d099"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="LA121090-0095"
SELECTOR="E"
SUMMARIZER="C">

The 1990 San Diego Marathon was run on the North County course. It was the first 
marathon to be run there. Contestants liked the new course. The marathon was run in 
beautiful weather, with warm breezes and 74-degree readings.

Over 4,000 runners participated, but the field was considered to be a weak one. Benjamin 
Martinez of Mexico was the men's winner. Kathy Smith of Newport Beach was the 
fastest woman. Each received two thousand dollars for the victory. Both are relatively 
new to running the marathon distance of 26.2 miles, and for each it was the first marathon 
victory.</SUM>

